<span id="v.ii.xviii"></span>

### <span id="v.ii.xviii-p0.1"></span>Chapter XVIII.—The glory of the cross.

<span id="v.ii.xviii-p1"></span><span id="v.ii.xviii-p1.1"></span>Let my
spirit be counted as nothing <span id="fr_605"></span>[606](#fn_605.md) for
the sake of the cross, which is a stumbling-block <span
id="fr_606"></span>[607](#fn_606.md) to those that do not believe, but to
us salvation and <span id="page_57">p. 57</span> <span
id="v.ii.xviii-Page_57"></span> life eternal. “Where is the wise man?
where the disputer?” <span id="fr_607"></span>[608](#fn_607.md) Where is
the boasting of those who are styled prudent? <span
id="v.ii.xviii-p4.2"></span><span id="v.ii.xviii-p4.3"></span>For our
God, Jesus Christ, was, according to the appointment <span
id="fr_608"></span>[609](#fn_608.md) of God, conceived in the womb by Mary,
of the seed of David, but by the Holy Ghost. He was born and baptized,
that by His passion He might purify the water.

<span id="v.ii.xviii-p6"></span><span id="v.ii.xviii-p6.1"></span>The
cross of Christ is indeed a stumbling-block to those that do not
believe, but to the believing it is salvation and life eternal. “Where
is the wise man? where the disputer?” <span
id="fr_609"></span>[610](#fn_609.md) Where is the boasting of those who are
called mighty? <span id="v.ii.xviii-p7.2"></span><span
id="v.ii.xviii-p7.3"></span>For the Son of God, who was begotten before
time began, <span id="fr_610"></span>[611](#fn_610.md) and established all
things according to the will of the Father, He was conceived in the womb
of Mary, according to the appointment of God, of the seed of David, and
by the Holy Ghost. For says \[the Scripture\], “Behold, a virgin shall
be with child, and shall bring forth a son, and He shall be called
Immanuel.” <span id="fr_611"></span>[612](#fn_611.md) He was born and was
baptized by John, that He might ratify the institution committed to that
prophet.

